  "derivation_layer": {
    "source_latex": "% BEGIN TZP DERIVATION LAYER\n\\tzpsection{Derivation Layer}\n\\paragraph{Primary Statement.}\n\nQuantum entanglement between two regions in a Trawinistic manifold can be quantified by the von Neumann entropy.\n\n\\paragraph{Primary Derivation.}\n\nFor a bipartition of the system into subsystems $A$ and $B$, let $\\rho_A = \\mathrm{Tr}_B\\,\\rho$ denote the reduced density matrix of $A$.  The entanglement entropy is\n\n\\begin{equation}\nS_A = -\\mathrm{Tr}\\big( \\rho_A\\log\\rho_A \\big).\n\\end{equation}\n\nIn Trawin geometry, $S_A$ typically obeys an area law with subleading corrections dependent on the curvature near the zero point.\n\n\\paragraph{Interpretation.}\n\nEntanglement reflects topological connections between regions.  At the TZP the area law may receive corrections from the lemniscatic self‑intersection and metric degeneracy.\n% END TZP DERIVATION LAYER"
  },
